# Type System Governance

⚠️ **ALL types and interfaces MUST be defined in the `/types` directory.**

## Canonical Locations

| Type Category   | Location                             | Examples                         |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------ | -------------------------------- |
| Shared UI types | `types/common.ts`                    | NavigationItem, SocialLinks      |
| Component props | `types/props.ts`                     | ButtonProps, CardProps           |
| API DTOs        | `types/api/*.ts`                     | EventDTO, CitySummaryResponseDTO |
| Domain types    | `types/event.ts`, `types/filters.ts` | FilterState, EventFilters        |
| URL types       | `types/url-filters.ts`               | URLFilterState, RouteSegments    |

## Before Creating a Type

1. Search `types/` for existing types
2. Check `types/README.md` for organization patterns
3. If extending, use `Pick`, `Omit`, or `extends`
4. Place in the most appropriate canonical file

## ESLint Enforces This

You will get lint errors for inline types outside `/types`.

